President Joe Biden spoke with Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan, President of the United Arab Emirates, to celebrate the clean energy cooperation framework signed by both countries. The partnership, called the "Partnership for Accelerating Clean Energy" (PACE), aims to generate 100 new gigawatts of clean energy and spur $100 billion in financing and support. President Biden thanked President bin Zayed for his leadership on climate issues and pledged support for the UAE's hosting of the 28th session of the Conference of the Parties (COP-28) in 2023. The United States and the UAE will collaborate on various clean energy initiatives, including carbon and methane management, civil nuclear energy, and decarbonizing the industrial and transport sectors. Both leaders also emphasized the importance of deepening the strategic relationship between the two countries.